        "heading": "Learn more about the Retro Series",
        "content": "<p>Understand <strong>3-layer composite steel</strong> construction and why it delivers the best of both worlds — a hard cutting core wrapped in tough, corrosion-resistant cladding. <a href=\"/blogs/news/san-mai-construction-guide\">San Mai construction guide</a></p><p>How does <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel</strong> compare to VG10? Our detailed analysis covers edge retention, toughness, and real-world performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/vg10-steel-vs-10cr15comov-guide\">VG10 vs 10Cr15CoMoV comparison</a></p><p>What does <strong>HRC 60 hardness</strong> actually mean for your kitchen? Learn how Rockwell hardness affects sharpness, durability, and maintenance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Simple daily habits that keep your Retro Series knives performing at their best — from proper cutting boards to storage tips. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-care-daily-maintenance-guide\">Daily knife care guide</a></p><p>New to quality knives? The <strong>Supreme Series</strong> offers a durable German steel entry point at a lower price. <a href=\"/collections/hezhen-supreme-series-knives\">Shop the Supreme Series</a></p><p>Compare all Xinzuo and Hezhen knife series side by side — steel, hardness, handles, and pricing. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-series-comparison-guide\">Full series comparison guide</a></p>",
